<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - AIR SYSTEM - SELECTOR VALVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SELECTOR VALVE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301816">Figure 16</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal and Disassembly</title>
            <figure id="f1301816" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301816" filename="../figg13/G1301816.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Selector Valve Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect all air lines to the valve. Loosen the jam nut securing the valve to the gear
                    shift lever and turn the valve from the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the three screws from the bottom of the valve body and remove the top cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the actuator (control button) from the cover post and the springs, seals, O-rings
                    and detent parts from the actuator.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Reassembly and Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301816">Figure 16</hotlnk>
                    for proper reassembly. Use a VERY SMALL amount of silicone lubricant on the O-rings to avoid
                    clogging the ports.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air lines with their sheathing and O-rings on the gear shift lever.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the jam nut and valve on the lever. Use the nut to lock the valve in position
                    with control button on the driver's side.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the 1/8 inch O.D. air line from the Center Port of the splitter cylinder cover
                    to "D" Port; air line from the tee fitting at the High Range or "H" Port of the slave valve to "S"
                    Port.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
